17#include <config.h>
18
19#include <inttypes.h>
20#include <stdbool.h>
21
22#include <isc/mem.h>
23#include <isc/ratelimiter.h>
24#include <isc/task.h>
25#include <isc/time.h>
26#include <isc/timer.h>
27#include <isc/util.h>
28
29typedef enum {
30 isc_ratelimiter_stalled = 0,
31 isc_ratelimiter_ratelimited = 1,
32 isc_ratelimiter_idle = 2,
33 isc_ratelimiter_shuttingdown = 3
34} isc_ratelimiter_state_t;
35
36struct isc_ratelimiter {
37 isc_mem_t * mctx;
38 isc_mutex_t lock;
39 int refs;
40 isc_task_t * task;
41 isc_timer_t * timer;
42 isc_interval_t interval;
43 uint32_t pertic;
44 bool pushpop;
45 isc_ratelimiter_state_t state;
46 isc_event_t shutdownevent;
47 ISC_LIST(isc_event_t) pending;
48};
49
50#define ISC_RATELIMITEREVENT_SHUTDOWN (ISC_EVENTCLASS_RATELIMITER + 1)
51
52static void
53ratelimiter_tick(isc_task_t *task, isc_event_t *event);
54
55static void
56ratelimiter_shutdowncomplete(isc_task_t *task, isc_event_t *event);
57
58isc_result_t
59isc_ratelimiter_create(isc_mem_t *mctx, isc_timermgr_t *timermgr,
60 isc_task_t *task, isc_ratelimiter_t **ratelimiterp)
61{
62 isc_result_t result;
63 isc_ratelimiter_t *rl;
64 INSIST(ratelimiterp != NULL && *ratelimiterp == NULL);
65
66 rl = isc_mem_get(mctx, sizeof(*rl));
67 if (rl == NULL)
68 return ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
69 rl->mctx = mctx;
70 rl->refs = 1;
71 rl->task = task;
72 isc_interval_set(&rl->interval, 0, 0);
73 rl->timer = NULL;
74 rl->pertic = 1;
75 rl->pushpop = false;
76 rl->state = isc_ratelimiter_idle;
77 ISC_LIST_INIT(rl->pending);
78
79 isc_mutex_init(&rl->lock);
80
81 result = isc_timer_create(timermgr, isc_timertype_inactive,
82 NULL, NULL, rl->task, ratelimiter_tick,
83 rl, &rl->timer);
84 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
85 goto free_mutex;
86
87 /*
88 * Increment the reference count to indicate that we may
89 * (soon) have events outstanding.
90 */
91 rl->refs++;
92
93 ISC_EVENT_INIT(&rl->shutdownevent,
94 sizeof(isc_event_t),
95 0, NULL, ISC_RATELIMITEREVENT_SHUTDOWN,
96 ratelimiter_shutdowncomplete, rl, rl, NULL, NULL);
97
98 *ratelimiterp = rl;
99 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
100
101free_mutex:
102 isc_mutex_destroy(&rl->lock);
103 isc_mem_put(mctx, rl, sizeof(*rl));
104 return (result);
105}
106
107isc_result_t
108isc_ratelimiter_setinterval(isc_ratelimiter_t *rl, isc_interval_t *interval) {
109 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
110
111 REQUIRE(rl != NULL);
112 REQUIRE(interval != NULL);
113
114 LOCK(&rl->lock);
115 rl->interval = *interval;
116 /*
117 * If the timer is currently running, change its rate.
118 */
119 if (rl->state == isc_ratelimiter_ratelimited) {
120 result = isc_timer_reset(rl->timer, isc_timertype_ticker, NULL,
121 &rl->interval, false);
122 }
123 UNLOCK(&rl->lock);
124 return (result);
125}
126
127void
128isc_ratelimiter_setpertic(isc_ratelimiter_t *rl, uint32_t pertic) {
129
130 REQUIRE(rl != NULL);
131
132 if (pertic == 0)
133 pertic = 1;
134 rl->pertic = pertic;
135}
136
137void
138isc_ratelimiter_setpushpop(isc_ratelimiter_t *rl, bool pushpop) {
139
140 REQUIRE(rl != NULL);
141
142 rl->pushpop = pushpop;
143}
144
145isc_result_t
146isc_ratelimiter_enqueue(isc_ratelimiter_t *rl, isc_task_t *task,
147 isc_event_t **eventp)
148{
149 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
150 isc_event_t *ev;
151
152 REQUIRE(rl != NULL);
153 REQUIRE(task != NULL);
154 REQUIRE(eventp != NULL && *eventp != NULL);
155 ev = *eventp;
156 REQUIRE(ev->ev_sender == NULL);
157
158 LOCK(&rl->lock);
159 if (rl->state == isc_ratelimiter_ratelimited ||
160 rl->state == isc_ratelimiter_stalled) {
161 ev->ev_sender = task;
162 *eventp = NULL;
163 if (rl->pushpop)
164 ISC_LIST_PREPEND(rl->pending, ev, ev_ratelink);
165 else
166 ISC_LIST_APPEND(rl->pending, ev, ev_ratelink);
167 } else if (rl->state == isc_ratelimiter_idle) {
168 result = isc_timer_reset(rl->timer, isc_timertype_ticker, NULL,
169 &rl->interval, false);
170 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
171 ev->ev_sender = task;
172 rl->state = isc_ratelimiter_ratelimited;
173 }
174 } else {
175 INSIST(rl->state == isc_ratelimiter_shuttingdown);
176 result = ISC_R_SHUTTINGDOWN;
177 }
178 UNLOCK(&rl->lock);
179 if (*eventp != NULL && result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
180 isc_task_send(task, eventp);
181 return (result);
182}
183
184isc_result_t
185isc_ratelimiter_dequeue(isc_ratelimiter_t *rl, isc_event_t *event) {
186 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
187
188 REQUIRE(rl != NULL);
189 REQUIRE(event != NULL);
190
191 LOCK(&rl->lock);
192 if (ISC_LINK_LINKED(event, ev_ratelink)) {
193 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(rl->pending, event, ev_ratelink);
194 event->ev_sender = NULL;
195 } else
196 result = ISC_R_NOTFOUND;
197 UNLOCK(&rl->lock);
198 return (result);
199}
200
201static void
202ratelimiter_tick(isc_task_t *task, isc_event_t *event) {
203 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
204 isc_ratelimiter_t *rl = (isc_ratelimiter_t *)event->ev_arg;
205 isc_event_t *p;
206 uint32_t pertic;
207
208 UNUSED(task);
209
210 isc_event_free(&event);
211
212 pertic = rl->pertic;
213 while (pertic != 0) {
214 pertic--;
215 LOCK(&rl->lock);
216 p = ISC_LIST_HEAD(rl->pending);
217 if (p != NULL) {
218 /*
219 * There is work to do. Let's do it after unlocking.
220 */
221 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(rl->pending, p, ev_ratelink);
222 } else {
223 /*
224 * No work left to do. Stop the timer so that we don't
225 * waste resources by having it fire periodically.
226 */
227 result = isc_timer_reset(rl->timer,
228 isc_timertype_inactive,
229 NULL, NULL, false);
230 RUNTIME_CHECK(result == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
231 rl->state = isc_ratelimiter_idle;
232 pertic = 0; /* Force the loop to exit. */
233 }
234 UNLOCK(&rl->lock);
235 if (p != NULL) {
236 isc_task_t *evtask = p->ev_sender;
237 isc_task_send(evtask, &p);
238 }
239 INSIST(p == NULL);
240 }
241}
242
243void
244isc_ratelimiter_shutdown(isc_ratelimiter_t *rl) {
245 isc_event_t *ev;
246 isc_task_t *task;
247
248 REQUIRE(rl != NULL);
249
250 LOCK(&rl->lock);
251 rl->state = isc_ratelimiter_shuttingdown;
252 (void)isc_timer_reset(rl->timer, isc_timertype_inactive,
253 NULL, NULL, false);
254 while ((ev = ISC_LIST_HEAD(rl->pending)) != NULL) {
255 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(rl->pending, ev, ev_ratelink);
256 ev->ev_attributes |= ISC_EVENTATTR_CANCELED;
257 task = ev->ev_sender;
258 isc_task_send(task, &ev);
259 }
260 isc_timer_detach(&rl->timer);
261
262 /*
263 * Send an event to our task. The delivery of this event
264 * indicates that no more timer events will be delivered.
265 */
266 ev = &rl->shutdownevent;
267 isc_task_send(rl->task, &ev);
268
269 UNLOCK(&rl->lock);
270}
271
272static void
273ratelimiter_shutdowncomplete(isc_task_t *task, isc_event_t *event) {
274 isc_ratelimiter_t *rl = (isc_ratelimiter_t *)event->ev_arg;
275
276 UNUSED(task);
277
278 isc_ratelimiter_detach(&rl);
279}
280
281static void
282ratelimiter_free(isc_ratelimiter_t *rl) {
283 isc_mutex_destroy(&rl->lock);
284 isc_mem_put(rl->mctx, rl, sizeof(*rl));
285}
286
287void
288isc_ratelimiter_attach(isc_ratelimiter_t *source, isc_ratelimiter_t **target) {
289
290 REQUIRE(source != NULL);
291 REQUIRE(target != NULL && *target == NULL);
292
293 LOCK(&source->lock);
294 REQUIRE(source->refs > 0);
295 source->refs++;
296 INSIST(source->refs > 0);
297 UNLOCK(&source->lock);
298 *target = source;
299}
300
301void
302isc_ratelimiter_detach(isc_ratelimiter_t **rlp) {
303 isc_ratelimiter_t *rl;
304 bool free_now = false;
305
306 REQUIRE(rlp != NULL && *rlp != NULL);
307
308 rl = *rlp;
309
310 LOCK(&rl->lock);
311 REQUIRE(rl->refs > 0);
312 rl->refs--;
313 if (rl->refs == 0)
314 free_now = true;
315 UNLOCK(&rl->lock);
316
317 if (free_now)
318 ratelimiter_free(rl);
319
320 *rlp = NULL;
321}
322
323isc_result_t
324isc_ratelimiter_stall(isc_ratelimiter_t *rl) {
325 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
326
327 REQUIRE(rl != NULL);
328
329 LOCK(&rl->lock);
330 switch (rl->state) {
331 case isc_ratelimiter_shuttingdown:
332 result = ISC_R_SHUTTINGDOWN;
333 break;
334 case isc_ratelimiter_ratelimited:
335 result = isc_timer_reset(rl->timer, isc_timertype_inactive,
336 NULL, NULL, false);
337 RUNTIME_CHECK(result == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
338 /* FALLTHROUGH */
339 case isc_ratelimiter_idle:
340 case isc_ratelimiter_stalled:
341 rl->state = isc_ratelimiter_stalled;
342 break;
343 }
344 UNLOCK(&rl->lock);
345 return (result);
346}
347
348isc_result_t
349isc_ratelimiter_release(isc_ratelimiter_t *rl) {
350 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
351
352 REQUIRE(rl != NULL);
353
354 LOCK(&rl->lock);
355 switch (rl->state) {
356 case isc_ratelimiter_shuttingdown:
357 result = ISC_R_SHUTTINGDOWN;
358 break;
359 case isc_ratelimiter_stalled:
360 if (!ISC_LIST_EMPTY(rl->pending)) {
361 result = isc_timer_reset(rl->timer,
362 isc_timertype_ticker, NULL,
363 &rl->interval, false);
364 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
365 rl->state = isc_ratelimiter_ratelimited;
366 } else
367 rl->state = isc_ratelimiter_idle;
368 break;
369 case isc_ratelimiter_ratelimited:
370 case isc_ratelimiter_idle:
371 break;
372 }
373 UNLOCK(&rl->lock);
374 return (result);
375}
